# Oracle Database Free with Docker and Spring Boot

## 1. Start Oracle Database in Docker

### Pull Oracle Database Free Image

```bash
docker pull container-registry.oracle.com/database/free:latest
```

### Create a Persistent Volume

```bash
docker volume create oracle-data
```

### Run Oracle Container

```bash
docker run -d \
  --name oracle-free \
  -p 1521:1521 \
  -p 5500:5500 \
  -e ORACLE_PWD=Oracle123 \
  -v oracle-data:/opt/oracle/oradata \
  container-registry.oracle.com/database/free:latest
```

### Verify Container Status

```bash
docker ps
```

### Check Database Startup Logs

```bash
docker logs -f oracle-free
```

Wait until you see:

```text
DATABASE IS READY TO USE!
```

---

## 2. Verify Oracle Database

Connect to the database:

```bash
docker exec -it oracle-free sqlplus system/Oracle123@FREEPDB1
```

List available pluggable databases:

```sql
SHOW PDBS;
```

Expected output:

```text
FREEPDB1
```

---

## 3. Spring Boot Configuration

### application.properties

```properties
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:oracle:thin:@//localhost:1521/FREEPDB1
spring.datasource.username=system
spring.datasource.password=Oracle123
spring.datasource.driver-class-name=oracle.jdbc.OracleDriver

spring.jpa.database-platform=org.hibernate.dialect.OracleDialect
spring.jpa.show-sql=true
spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=none
```

> Replace `Oracle123` with the password used in the `ORACLE_PWD` environment variable when the container was created.

---

## 4. Maven Dependency

```xml
<dependency>
    <groupId>com.oracle.database.jdbc</groupId>
    <artifactId>ojdbc11</artifactId>
    <scope>runtime</scope>
</dependency>
```

For Spring Boot 3 and Java 17+, `ojdbc11` is recommended.

